<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1811] DataImportHandler: dataimporter.functions.formatDate should have a redefined concept of NOW for each import</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1811</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&quot;The first argument can be a computed value eg: &apos;$&lt;/p&gt;
{dataimporter.functions.formatDate(&apos;NOW-3DAYS&apos;, &apos;yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm&apos;)}
&lt;p&gt;&apos;  and it uses the syntax of the datemath parser in Solr.&quot;  When using a relative date with NOW, NOW is set with teh first full-import but not with subsequent imports.  NOW should be redefined with each new import.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12458276">SOLR-1811</key>
            <summary>DataImportHandler: dataimporter.functions.formatDate should have a redefined concept of NOW for each import</summary>
